<topic id="xquery-transformation">
  <title>XQuery Transformation</title>
  <!--Proofed-->
  <body>
    <p>To create an <uicontrol>XQuery transformation</uicontrol> scenario, use one of the following
        methods:<ul id="ul_sgy_kzh_br">
        <li>Go to <menucascade>
            <uicontrol>Window</uicontrol>
            <uicontrol>Show View</uicontrol>
          </menucascade> and select <uicontrol><image href="../img/TransformConfig16.png"
              id="image_a53_rvv_sr"/>Transformation Scenarios</uicontrol> to display this view.
          Click the <uicontrol>New</uicontrol> button and select <uicontrol>XQuery
            transformation</uicontrol>.</li>
        <li>Use the <uicontrol><image href="../img/TransformConfig16.png" id="image_egn_rvv_sr"
            />Configure Transformation Scenario(s) (<shortcut
              conkeyref="reusable_oxygen_shortcuts_list/ctrl_shift_c_shortcut"
              product="author developer editor"/><shortcut
              conkeyref="reusable_oxygen_shortcuts_list/alt_shift_tc_shortcut"
              product="authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse"/>)</uicontrol> action from the
            <uicontrol>Transformation</uicontrol> toolbar or the <menucascade
            product="author developer editor">
            <uicontrol>Document</uicontrol>
            <uicontrol> Transformation</uicontrol>
          </menucascade><uicontrol product="authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse"
            >XML</uicontrol> menu. Then click the <uicontrol>New</uicontrol> button and select
            <uicontrol>XQuery transformation</uicontrol>.</li>
        <li>Use the <uicontrol><image href="../img/ApplyStyleSheet16.png" id="image_utw_2xs_1r"
            />Apply Transformation Scenario(s) (<shortcut
              conkeyref="reusable_oxygen_shortcuts_list/ctrl_shift_t_shortcut"
              product="author developer editor"/><shortcut
              conkeyref="reusable_oxygen_shortcuts_list/alt_shift_tt_shortcut"
              product="authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse"/>)</uicontrol> action from the
            <uicontrol>Transformation</uicontrol> toolbar or the <menucascade
            product="author developer editor">
            <uicontrol>Document</uicontrol>
            <uicontrol> Transformation</uicontrol>
          </menucascade><uicontrol product="authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse"
            >XML</uicontrol> menu. Then click the <uicontrol>New</uicontrol> button and select
            <uicontrol>XQuery transformation</uicontrol>.<note
            conkeyref="reusables-transforming-documents/note-001"/></li>
      </ul></p>
    <p>All three methods open the <uicontrol>New Scenario</uicontrol> dialog box. This dialog box
      allows you to configure the options that control the transformation. </p>
    <p conkeyref="reusables-transforming-documents/name-storage-options"
      product="author developer editor"/>
    <p>The lower part of the dialog box contains the following tabs:<ul>
        <li><xref href="the-xquery-tab.dita#the-xquery-tab"
              ><uicontrol>XQuery</uicontrol></xref></li>
        <li><xref
          href="fo-processor-tab--xml-xquery.dita#fo-processor-tab--xml-xquery"
              ><uicontrol>FO Processor</uicontrol></xref></li>
      <li><xref href="output-xml-xquery.dita#output-xml-xquery"
              ><uicontrol>Output</uicontrol></xref></li>
      </ul>
    </p>
  </body>
